summaries.short: Sookie hatches a dangerous plan; Pam looks to motivate Eric.
summaries.full: Sookie hatches a dangerous plan to take down the H-Vamps, even as Vince and his armed vigilantes pose an equally serious threat. Lafayette gets high with James; Jason eyes a family future with Violet; Willa is forced to find a new place to stay; Sarah Newlin sheds her past. Pam offers Eric a compelling reason to return to Louisiana--and be the vampire he used to be.

summaries.short: Sookie enlists a band of vampires and humans to track down the H-Vamps.
summaries.full: In the aftermath of yet another bloodbath, Sam, Sookie and Jason find themselves the bearers of bad news in Bon Temps and beyond. Pam recalls the events that led her and Eric to Shreveport and Fangtasia. Bill and Jessica get nourishment from unexpected sources. Following a new lead, Sookie enlists a band of vampires and humans to track down the H-Vamps.

summaries.short: Sookie and Jason visit an abandoned town in search of clues; Pam continues her search for Eric.
summaries.full: A trio of hostages taken in the Bellefleur's attack look to a familiar face as a possible liberator from the H-vamps. Sookie and Jason visit an abandoned town in search of clues. Lettie Mae turns to Willa in order to channel her family past. Vince whips his fellow vigilantes into a dangerous frenzy. Pam's search for her maker leads her to a very familiar place.

summaries.full: Relive Sn 7 / Ep 3 highlights of the HBO series 'True Blood.'

summaries.short: Sookie hosts a mainstreaming party; Eric and Pam head to Dallas for a fundraiser.
summaries.full: Exhausted from her recent travails, Sookie finds herself the unwilling host of a festive mainstreaming party in Bon Temps. In search of an elusive adversary, Eric and Pam head to Dallas and attend a gala fundraiser. Andy makes a life-changing decision; Jessica and James reach a crossroads; Bill loses himself in remembrance of human days.

summaries.short: Season Seven Premiere. Bon Temps is rocked by a vicious attack by a band of rogue H-vamps.
summaries.full: Season Seven Premiere. Rogue H-vamps crash the vampire-human mixer at Bellefleur's, with shocking results. As Sookie seeks refuge from accusations that, somehow, she's to blame for the chaos in Bon Temps, the "one vampire for every human" plan moves forward. In the face of a vigilante insurrection led by a redneck named Vince, Bill receives aid from an unexpected source.

summaries.short: Sookie makes a shocking discovery; Eric and Pam forge an unlikely alliance.
summaries.full: A shocking discovery forces Sookie to reassess her recent involvement with Bill. In Dallas, Eric and Pam forge an unlikely alliance in their hunt for a shared nemesis. Andy bickers with Holly about their children's behavior; Lafayette shares a vision with Lettie Mae; Jason owns up to his true feelings about Violet; Sam finds himself in a quandary regarding Nicole.

summaries.short: (Season Six Finale) Sookie asks Warlow to take things slower; Bill pays a price for salvation.
summaries.full: (Season Six Finale) Bill discovers that salvation comes at a price; Jason senses firsthand a vampire attraction. With the latest vampire crisis seemingly over, Sookie examines her future with Warlow while Bon Temps braces itself when a new crisis threatens both humans and vampires.
